There's a bug on Swap screen in the iOS app. It's been there since V3 was introduced, and is still present in the most recent build 389. The bug makes it impossible to swap values that are floating-point numbers like 0.0123.

When you try to Swap a fraction of a value, the input field expects period (".") as a decimal separator (eg. the valid number would be "0.0123"). But you're not able to enter the period character, as the numeric keyboard that is displayed when you tap on the input field contains only comma (",") decimal separator. You can enter the comma (eg. "0,0123"), but the Swap feature won't work (the values won't be calculated, the "Preview swap" button will be disabled).

Therefore, it is not currently possible to swap values that are floating point numbers. 

Maybe it's related to the phone's language / region / Number Format system settings. I have "English" language, "Poland" region and "1 234 567,89" Number Format.
